Wash and dry produce.

In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup}, @water{1 1/4%cups}, @Veggie Stock Concentrate{2}, @Turmeric{1/4%tsp}, and @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

> For perfect timing, start Step 3 when rice has 10 minutes left.

Meanwhile, halve, peel, and thinly slice @Red Onion{1/2}(sliced) into rings. Core, deseed, and dice @Long Green Pepper{1}(diced into 1/2-inch pieces). Roughly chop @Parsley{1/4%ounce}(chopped).

> Whole onion for 4 servings.

== Pickled Red Onion ==

In a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine sliced onion, @Red Wine Vinegar{5%tsp}, @Sugar{1/2%tsp}, and @salt{pinch}. Cover tightly with #plastic wrap{}, microwave until onion is bright pink, ~{1%minute}. Set aside.

> 1 tsp sugar for 4 servings.

== Paprika Turkey ==

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @Ground Turkey{10%ounce}, green pepper, and @Savory Paprika Blend{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @Pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and almost cooked through, ~{4%minutes}.

Add @Tomato Paste{1}(stirred in) and @water{1/4%cup}, cook, stirring, until pork is cooked through and liquid has mostly evaporated, ~{30-60%seconds} more. Remove from heat.

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

> Swap in beef or turkey for pork.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; divide between shallow #bowls{}. Top with pork and as much pickled onion (draining first) as you like. Garnish with parsley and serve.